      "updated": 1776671304422,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Topics that need to be mastered for LLD:-\n    . OOPS\n        -> classes\n        -> objects\n        -> Interfaces\n        -> Encapsulation\n        -> Abstraction\n        -> Inheritance\n            -> Association\n            -> Aggregation\n            -> Composition\n            -> Dependancy\n            -> Realization\n        -> Polymorphism\n    . SOLID\n        -> Single Responsibility Principle\n        -> Open Closed Principle\n        -> Liskov Substitution Principle\n        -> Interface Segregation Principle\n        -> Dependancy Inversion Principle\n    . Design Patterns\n        -> Creational DP\n            -> Factory \n            -> Singleton\n            -> prototype\n            -> Builder\n        -> Structural DP\n            -> Adapter\n            -> Decorator\n            -> Facade\n            -> Composite\n        -> Behaviourial DP\n            -> Chain of Resp\n            -> Command\n            -> Iterator\n            -> State\n            -> Strategy\n            -> Observer\n    . Parameters that must be fulfilled in order to justify one LLD Design:-\n\n        -> Scalabilty:- current code impl. should handle new features cleanly.\n        -> Latency:- Algorithmic complexity at code level.\n        -> Error/Edge Cases Handling:- How your code handles failures.\n        -> Concurrency:- How your code handles when multiples Processes/Threads spawns \n        -> Consistency:- How your code handles correctness of data.\n        -> Readable:- How your code is read and understand by another Engineers.\n        -> Testability:- How your packages/module/classes/methods are tested easily.\n        -> Maintainability:- How your packages/module/classes/methods are mainteained over time.\n        -> Extendibility:- How your classes are extended when new feature arrives OCP.\n\n\n",
      "fontSize": 20.008151506651362,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Topics that need to be mastered for LLD:-\n    . OOPS\n        -> classes\n        -> objects\n        -> Interfaces\n        -> Encapsulation\n        -> Abstraction\n        -> Inheritance\n            -> Association\n            -> Aggregation\n            -> Composition\n            -> Dependancy\n            -> Realization\n        -> Polymorphism\n    . SOLID\n        -> Single Responsibility Principle\n        -> Open Closed Principle\n        -> Liskov Substitution Principle\n        -> Interface Segregation Principle\n        -> Dependancy Inversion Principle\n    . Design Patterns\n        -> Creational DP\n            -> Factory \n            -> Singleton\n            -> prototype\n            -> Builder\n        -> Structural DP\n            -> Adapter\n            -> Decorator\n            -> Facade\n            -> Composite\n        -> Behaviourial DP\n            -> Chain of Resp\n            -> Command\n            -> Iterator\n            -> State\n            -> Strategy\n            -> Observer\n    . Parameters that must be fulfilled in order to justify one LLD Design:-\n\n        -> Scalabilty:- current code impl. should handle new features cleanly.\n        -> Latency:- Algorithmic complexity at code level.\n        -> Error/Edge Cases Handling:- How your code handles failures.\n        -> Concurrency:- How your code handles when multiples Processes/Threads spawns \n        -> Consistency:- How your code handles correctness of data.\n        -> Readable:- How your code is read and understand by another Engineers.\n        -> Testability:- How your packages/module/classes/methods are tested easily.\n        -> Maintainability:- How your packages/module/classes/methods are mainteained over time.\n        -> Extendibility:- How your classes are extended when new feature arrives OCP.\n\n\n",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
