      ],
      "updated": 1776742990859,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": ". Domain Driven Design:-\n\n    -> Read Feature Docs carefully.\n    -> Find Use cases and create User journey.\n    -> Find Domains/Entities.\n    -> Implement all Invariants on domains.\n    -> group domains to Aggregates.\n    -> Establish Relationships among Aggregates.\n    -> Define Responsibilities of each Aggregates.\n    -> Identify Domain CLasses.\n    -> Implement Service Layer for each Aggregate.\n    -> Implement Repository Layer.\n    -> Implement Controllers/API specs.\n    -> When Above steps are done, you should have\n        -> class Diagrams\n        -> ER Diagrams\n        -> User Journey/Avctivity Diagram\n        -> Code Directory Structure and Framework/Language in place\n    -> ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": ". Domain Driven Design:-\n\n    -> Read Feature Docs carefully.\n    -> Find Use cases and create User journey.\n    -> Find Domains/Entities.\n    -> Implement all Invariants on domains.\n    -> group domains to Aggregates.\n    -> Establish Relationships among Aggregates.\n    -> Define Responsibilities of each Aggregates.\n    -> Identify Domain CLasses.\n    -> Implement Service Layer for each Aggregate.\n    -> Implement Repository Layer.\n    -> Implement Controllers/API specs.\n    -> When Above steps are done, you should have\n        -> class Diagrams\n        -> ER Diagrams\n        -> User Journey/Avctivity Diagram\n        -> Code Directory Structure and Framework/Language in place\n    -> ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
